text: 125 is the natural number after 124 and before 126 and is an odd number. It is divisible by 1, 5, 25, and 125. == In mathematics == * 125 is the cube of 5. It can be expressed as a sum of two squares in two different ways, 125 = 10^2 + 5^2 = 11^2 + 2^2. * It is a Friedman number in base 10, since 125 = 51 + 2. Category:Integers
title: 125 (number)
